The paper discusses the use of Genetic Algorithms (GAs) and Bayesian Optimization Algorithms (BOA) to solve scheduling problems, which are common in the field of Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI). The paper also mentions the use of Learning Classifier Systems (LCS), which is a subfield of Machine Learning (cs.LG). The paper's focus on optimization and decision-making also suggests that it could fall under Robotics (cs.RO) and Systems and Control (cs.SY). Finally, the paper's emphasis on real-world applications and constraints suggests that it could also fall under Computer Engineering (cs.CE).
